The federal anti-drug strategy hasn’t worked. Drug production in foreign countries remains at high levels, with plentiful supplies available for export to the United States. Only a fraction of the drugs smuggled into the country are intercepted; it’s still relatively easy to get drugs acrossthe border and sell them to American customers. Furthermore, the enormous profits of drug trafficking continue to attract an endless stream of entrepreneurs who see opportunities far outweighing those offered by legitimate business.
